Press Releases.Title: 6 New Cases of Locally Transmitted Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 5 October 2020, 12 pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminary confirmed 6 new cases of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection. Based on our investigations so far, 1 is in the community, and 5 reside in dormitories.

2.          In addition, there is 1 imported case, who had been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore.

3.           We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.
